Citation.sAbstract: The heat capacity of crystalline 1-aminoadamantane over the temperature range from (5 to 370) K, the temperatures and the enthalpies of its solid-to-solid phase transitions, Ttrs,1 = (241.4 +- 0.2) K and Dtrs;1H m 1/4 o1716 10P J mol 1; Ttrs,2 = (284.6 +- 0.1) K and Dtrs;2H m 1/4 o5309 5P J mol 1, were obtained by the adiabatic calorimetry. The thermodynamic functions of the compound in the crystalline state were derived. The saturated vapour pressure and the sublimation enthalpy fDsubH mo298:15 KP 1/4 o61:65 0:63P kJ mol 1g were determined from the results of the measurements by the effusion Knudsen method and by the transpiration method. The enthalpy of combustion and the enthalpy of formation for crystalline 1-aminoadamantane were measured in a static-bomb isoperibol combustion calorimeter: DcH mocr;298:15 KP 1/4 o 6169:2 1:9P kJ mol 1 and DfH mocr;298:15 KP 1/4 o 195:4 2:3P kJ mol 1. The thermodynamic properties in the ideal gaseous state were calculated by the statistical thermodynamics method. The molecular and spectral data for 1-aminoadamantane were obtained from quantum-chemical calculations (B3LYP/6-31+G*) and from Raman and i.r. spectroscopic studies.
